<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="61">Geographic Range</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="61">Amazonian Brazil to southern Mexico.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="61">Biology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="61">This species occurs in wet climate areas, from sea level to 1200m elevation. In mature forest areas it is a common species under epiphytes in the canopy, although its minute size makes it easy to overlook. It also occurs on trees in synanthropic habitats such as coffee farms and city parks.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
